        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá≤üáΩ Mexico - Google lawsuit.</strong> Mexico has sued Google for renaming the Gulf of Mexico as the "Gulf of America" on US Google Maps. They argue this mislabels its territorial waters. Despite protests, Google cites a consistent global map policy. Mexico‚Äôs foreign ministry had previously sent letters to Google asking it not to re-label the Gulf of Mexico (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-13-may-25-worldwide-11-lawsuits-follow-google" target="_blank">lawsuits follow Google</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáÆüá≥ India - Modi‚Äôs address to the nation.</strong> PM Narendra Modi said Operation Sindoor has set up an alternate normal. He added that India will not tolerate nuclear blackmail and terrorist attacks and that it will not differentiate between the government sponsoring terrorism and the masterminds of terrorism during precision strikes. 78 personnel from both the country‚Äôs army and the air force sustained injuries during the four days of heightened tensions (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-13-may-25-worldwide-12-stern-warning" target="_blank">stern warning</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáÆüá± Israel- American hostage returned.</strong> American-Israeli soldier Edan Alexander was released by Hamas on Monday, after over 18 months in captivity. Captured during the October 7, 2023, attack, his release followed US-Hamas negotiations. A temporary pause in Israeli operations ensured his safe transfer. Alexander was the last known living American hostage (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-13-may-25-worldwide-13-more-about-the-release" target="_blank">more about the release</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá©üá™ Germany - 60 years of Israeli relations.</strong> Israeli President Isaac Herzog is visiting Germany to mark 60 years of diplomatic relations, amid tensions over Israel‚Äôs war in Gaza. While Germany affirms its support for Israel, criticism of the Gaza war and concerns about anti-Semitism complicate the relationship (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-13-may-25-worldwide-14-the-complex-relationship" target="_blank">the complex relationship</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá≥üá¨ Nigeria- Land disputes.</strong> 
           Unidentified gunmen killed 23 people in four separate attacks across villages in Benue state, central Nigeria. The violence, rooted in longstanding land disputes between herders and farmers, adds to mounting tension in the region. Ethnic and religious divisions, and environmental stress, often fuel these clashes (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-13-may-25-worldwide-15-the-turf-wars" target="_blank">the turf wars</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáµüá≠ Philippines - Elections.</strong> 
           Rodrigo Duterte triumphed in the Davao mayoral race despite his detention by the International Criminal Court. He garnered over 660,000 votes, eight times higher than his closest rival. Meanwhile, his daughter, VP Sara Duterte, faces possible impeachment, intensifying her feud with President Marcos Jr. (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-13-may-25-worldwide-16-political-theater" target="_blank">political theater</a>). 
          </p>
          
